"script": "Every single day, roughly 100 tons of space dust and tiny meteorites silently rain down onto the Earth. That's the weight of a fully loaded jumbo jet, falling from the sky as invisible specks. You see, most of these grains are smaller than a sand particle, burning up as the shooting stars you spot at night. And over a year, that's nearly 40,000 tons of cosmic material settling onto rooftops, oceans, and your own backyard. So some of the dust on your windowsill right now traveled millions of miles through space, just to land on your house.",
